<h4>Q: Figure Basing?</h4>
<p>As seen above, a "base" of close order Infantry represents up to 450 men, and covers a frontage of 100 paces. Depending on how many figures you can afford to put on the table, you need to work around this and work out what looks best for you.</p>
<p>A base of cavalry of the same frontage as an infantry base represents a half squadron of cavalry in open battle order. That is up to 75 horsemen in 1,2, or 3 ranks.</p>
<p>A base of skirmishers represents a platoon / half company of skirmishers, (40-60 men) and has the same 100 pace frontage as a half-battalion.</p>
<p>A base of Artillery represents a half-battery of guns (4 guns), with each gun spaced roughly 20 paces apart. Your basing should allow a full battery of 2 gun bases to have a total frontage of around 150 paces. (ie - more than a half-battalion infantry base, but less than 2 infantry bases).  For example: If your infantry bases are 40mm wide, then your artillery bases work well at 30mm wide.</p>
<p>Each base of figures should ideally be of the same size, although its easy enough to accomodate multiple basing schemes on the table at the same time without creating geometry problems.</p>

<p>If in doubt, always choose aesthetics over common sense and practicality.</p>

<p>Here are some examples :</p>
<ul>
	<li>GdB basing - 8 infantry figures in 2 ranks of 4. Each base here works fine for a half-battalion, and looks great too.</li>
	<li>Maurice basing - 6 infantry figures in 2 ranks of 3. You can use this as-is for a large battle, or consider 2 of these bases side by side as being a half-battalion.</li>
	<li>NaW basing - 4 infantry figures in 2 ranks of 2. Works best if you consider each 2x2 base to be a company, and consider pairs of NaW bases side by side to be half-battalions.</li>
	<li>Empire basing - 3 infantry figures in 1 rank. Works best if you consider each 3x1 base to be a company, and consider pairs of these one behind the other to be a half battalion. Even better - consider these to be platoon bases, and have groups of 4 considered to be half battalion.</li>
</ul>
<p></p>

